The death toll from the London tower block fire has risen to at least 30 and police are considering whether criminal offences had been committed, a senior police officer said on Friday.&#8220;We know that at least 30 people have died as a result of this fire,&#8221; said Commander Stuart Cundy, adding that the figure was expected to rise.He added that 24 people were still in hospital and 12 were receiving critical care.&#8220;The investigation will look in into what criminal offences may have been committed,&#8221; Cundy said.-Reuters 